	YOU CAN EDIT THIS FILE TO CREATE YOUR OWN GAME IN A FEW HOURS! 

	If you want to create your own Laserdisc game using SINGE, you just need to have some videos and then to edit this file. It's really easy, most of the work is already done. Just read my comments. The file is quite long but you probably don't need to fill everything (if you've got less than 10 levels or less than 40 death).


	3 EASY STEPS TO CREATE YOUR GAME :

	1) General settings like Labels, Color, Scoring, etc... (5 minutes to fill this) 

	2) Declare the frames for the different videos of your game (5 to 20 minutes if you've got many death scenes).

	3) Declare the moves within each Level/Scene. This is the longest part (a few hours) but it's funny because this is where you turn your lifeless movie into a game!  

	In fact the most difficult part is to find/edit the videos. Once you've got them, you can turn them into a game in a few hours. Give it a try!
	Inside his release, you'll find a blank setupgame.singe for your needs with all levels and all segments included. Just fill it !

	VIDEOS :

	You will need a program (like Adobe Premiere) to check the frames of your movies. You'll need :

	- One short video showing the title of your game (of course it can be a static image and it's optional)

	- One "attract" video (actually you can have up to 3 different).

	- One video per level of your game (maximum 10). 

	- One video for the menu (Game Over, Continue, etc).

	- One video for the various death (up to 40).

	Note : You can have a total of 65536 frames (between 36 and 45 minutes, depending on the FPS). 
	Avoid too long video files cause Daphne will have some trouble to parse files over 2Go.

]]--


